## Figure vs Plot

This confuses everyone.  
Imagine a photo frame.  
The frame is Figure  
inside the frame : Graph  

Figure  
│  
├──Axes  
│   ├──Line  
│   ├──Scatter Points  
│   ├──Text  
│   ├──Legend  
│   ├──Axis  
│   └──Grid  

When you call show(), Matplotlib asks each artist to render itself.  

| Plot | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| Line Plot | How values change over time |
| Scatter Plot | Relationship between two variables |
| Bar Chart | Compare categories |
| Histogram | Distribution of data |
| Pie Chart | Parts of a whole (use sparingly) |
| Box Plot | Spread and outliers |
| Violin Plot | Distribution shape |
| Heatmap | Values across a matrix |
| Error Bar Plot | Measurement uncertainty |

## Why Learn the Object-Oriented API?

For simple scripts:  
plt.plot(...)is fine.  
For projects with multiple subplots, dashboards, or reusable code:
fig, ax = plt.subplots()  
ax.plot(...)  
